s a city in [[Kodiak Island Borough, Alaska]], United States. At the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]] the population was 87, down from 115 in 2000.\n\n==Geography==\nLarsen Bay is located at {{coord|57|32|12|N|153|59|29|W|type:city}} (57.536651, -153.991440).<ref name=\"GR1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/geographies/reference-files/time-series/geo/gazetteer-files.html|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2011-04-23|date=2011-02-12|title=US Gazetteer files: 2010, 2000, and 1990}}</ref>\n\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the city has a total area of {{convert|7.6|sqmi|km2}}, of which, {{convert|5.4|sqmi|km2}} of it is land and {{convert|2.2|sqmi|km2}} of it (28.7%) is water.\n\n===Climate===\n{{Weather box\n| collapsed =\n| location = Larsen Bay, Alaska\n| single line = Y\n| Jan record high F = 55\n| Feb record high F = 53\n| Mar record high F = 56\n| Apr record high F = 65\n| May record high F = 83\n| Jun record high F = 83\n| Jul record high F = 78\n| Aug record high F = 76\n| Sep record high F = 72\n| Oct record high F = 64\n| Nov record high F = 53\n| Dec record high F = 49\n|year record high F = \n| Jan high F = 35.1\n| Feb high F = 36.5\n| Mar high F = 38.4\n| Apr high F = 43.3\n| May high F = 51.6\n| Jun high F = 60.0\n| Jul high F = 63.1\n| Aug high F = 61.4\n| Sep high F = 57.3\n| Oct high F = 45.7\n| Nov high F = 39.7\n| Dec high F = 33.9\n|year high F = \n|Jan mean F = 28.7\n|Feb mean F = 29.7\n|Mar mean F = 31.6\n|Apr mean F = 35.5\n|May mean F = 42.9\n|Jun mean F = 50.9\n|Jul mean F = 54.9\n|Aug mean F = 54.3\n|Sep mean F = 50.0\n|Oct mean F = 39.0\n|Nov mean F = 33.5\n|Dec mean F = 27.6\n|year mean F = \n| Jan low F = 22.2\n| Feb low F = 22.8\n| Mar low F = 24.8\n| Apr low F = 27.7\n| May low F = 34.2\n| Jun low F = 41.7\n| Jul low F = 46.6\n| Aug low F = 47.2\n| Sep low F = 42.6\n| Oct low F = 32.3\n| Nov low F = 27.3\n| Dec low F = 21.3\n|year low F = \n| Jan record low F = \u22125\n| Feb record low F = \u221215\n| Mar record low F = -5\n| Apr record low F = 2\n| May record low F = 15\n| Jun record low F = 28\n| Jul record low F = 34\n| Aug record low F = 35\n| Sep record low F = 24\n| Oct record low F = 10\n| Nov record low F = -1\n| Dec record low F = -3\n|year record low F =\n\n|precipitation colour = green\n| Jan precipitation inch = 2.09\n| Feb precipitation inch = 1.47\n| Mar precipitation inch = 1.54\n| Apr precipitation inch = 1.06\n| May precipitation inch = 0.76\n| Jun precipitation inch = 1.10\n| Jul precipitation inch = 1.17\n| Aug precipitation inch = 2.55\n| Sep precipitation inch = 2.88\n| Oct precipitation inch = 2.64\n| Nov precipitation inch = 2.85\n| Dec precipitation inch = 1.95\n|year precipitation inch =\n\n|Jan snow inch = 3.7\n|Feb snow inch = 4.4\n|Mar snow inch = 3.6\n|Apr snow inch = 0.7\n|May snow inch = 0.3\n|Jun snow inch = 0.0\n|Jul snow inch = 0.0\n|Aug snow inch = 0.0\n|Sep snow inch = 0.0\n|Oct snow inch = 0.4\n|Nov snow inch = 1.6\n|Dec snow inch = 4.1\n|year snow inch = \n|source 1 = WRCC <ref name=\"climate\">[https://wrcc.dri.edu/cgi-bin/cliMAIN.pl?ak5425 Larsen Bay, Alaska - Period of Record : 9/1/1939 to 11/30/1993] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170525124229/http://wrcc.dri.edu/cgi-bin/cliMAIN.pl?ak5425 |date=2017-05-25 }}. Retrieved November 15, 2019.</ref>\n|date=October 2019}}\n\n==Demographics==\n{{US Census population\n|1940= 38\n|1950= 53\n|1960= 72\n|1970= 109\n|1980= 168\n|1990= 147\n|2000= 115\n|2010= 87\n|estyear=2018\n|estimate=85\n|estref=<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2018.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=June 4, 2019}}</ref>\n|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref name=\"DecennialCensus\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/decennial-census.html|title=Census of Population and Housing|publisher=Census.gov|accessdate=June 4, 2015}}</ref>\n}}\nLarsen Bay first appeared on the 1940 U.S. Census as an unincorporated village. It formally incorporated as a city in 1974.\n\nAs of the census<ref name=\"GR2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, there were 115 people, 40 households, and 26 families residing in the city. The population density was 21.1 people per square mile (8.2/km\u00b2). There were 70 housing units at an average density of 12.9 per square&nbsp;mile (5.0/km\u00b2). The racial makeup of the city was 20.87% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 78.26% [[Race (United States Census)|Native American]], and 0.87% from two or more races.\n\nThere were 40 households out of which 42.5% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 45.0% were married couples living together, 12.5% had a female householder with no husband present, and 35.0% were non-families. 27.5% of all households were made up of individuals and 5.0% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.88 and the average family size was 3.54.\n\nIn the city, the age distribution of the population shows 38.3% under the age of 18, 4.3% from 18 to 24, 28.7% from 25 to 44, 19.1% from 45 to 64, and 9.6% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 29 years. For every 100 females, there were 113.0 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 102.9 males.\n\nThe median income for a household in the city was $40,833, and the median income for a family was $30,000. Males had a median income of $31,250 versus $50,625 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the city was $16,227. There were 27.3% of families and 20.5% of the population living below the [[poverty line]], including 22.6% of under eighteen and 33.3% of those over 64.\n\n==Education==\nThe Larsen Bay School, a K-12 rural school, is operated by the [[Kodiak Island Borough School District]].<ref>\"[http://www.kibsd.org/domain/304 Our Schools].\" [[Kodiak Island Borough School District]]. Retrieved on February 15, 2017.</ref> The school was closed for the 2018-2019 school year.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kodiak School District Moves to Close Larsen Bay School |url=https://www.usnews.com/news/best-states/alaska/articles/2018-09-22/kodiak-school-district-moves-to-close-larsen-bay-school |accessdate=December 12, 2018 |publisher=USNews |date=September 22, 2018 |ref=https://www.usnews.com/news/best-states/alaska/articles/2018-09-22/kodiak-school-district-moves-to-close-larsen-bay-school}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Kodiak Island Borough, Alaska}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Cities in Alaska]]\n[[Category:Cities in Kodiak Island Borough, Alaska]]\n[[Category:Populated coastal places in Alaska]]\n[[Category:Road-inaccessible communities of Alaska]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|City in Alaska, United States}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name            = Larsen Bay\n|native_name            = Uyaqsaq\n|settlement_type          = [[City (Alaska)|City]]\n|nickname                 = \n|motto                    = \n<!-- Images -->\n|image_skyline            = \n|imagesize                = \n|image_caption            = \n|image_flag               = \n|image_seal               = \n<!-- Maps -->\n|pushpin_map                = Alaska\n|pushpin_map_caption              = Location in Alaska\n|image_map              = \n|mapsize                 = \n|map_caption            = \n<!-- Location -->\n|coordinates              = {{coord|57|32|12|N|153|59|29|W|region:US_type:city|display=inline,title}}\n|subdivision_type         = Country\n|subdivision_name         = United States\n|subdivision_type1        = [[U.S. state|State]]\n|subdivision_name1        = [[Alaska]]\n|subdivision_type2        = [[List of boroughs and census areas in Alaska|Borough]]\n|subdivision_name2        = [[Kodiak Island Borough, Alaska|Kodiak Island]]\n|government_footnotes     = \n|government_type          = \n|leader_title      